 Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Poultney","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Pountney  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Pountney","meanings":["English: locative name from Poultney (Leics), which is recorded as  <i>Pontenei</i> in 1086 and  <i>Pulteney</i> in 1220. The place-name derives from an Old English personal name * <i>Pulta</i> (genitive * <i>Pultan</i>) + Old English  <i>ēg</i> ‘island, piece of dry ground in a fen’."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Ellen De Poultney was born about 1296. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with William de Poultney."},"et":{"Abt 1296  –":"umbes 1296–Surnud","1292–1360":"1292–1360","1318–1385":"1318–1385","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1322–Male":"1322–Surnud","1328–1371":"1328–1371","1296–Female":"1296–Surnud","1385":"1385","1296":"1296","Abt 1296  ":"umbes 1296","1371":"1371","1360":"1360","Abt 1318":"umbes 1318","1292":"1292","1322":"1322","1320":"1320","Abt 1320 ":"umbes 1320","Abt 1322 Of, Misterton, Leic, England":"umbes 1322","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Misterton, Leicestershire, England":"Misterton, Leicestershire, England","Leicestershire England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Misterton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Misterton, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1296  –":"noin 1296–Kuollut","1292–1360":"1292–1360","1318–1385":"1318–1385","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1322–Male":"1322–Kuollut","1328–1371":"1328–1371","1296–Female":"1296–Kuollut","1385":"1385","1296":"1296","Abt 1296  ":"noin 1296","1371":"1371","1360":"1360","Abt 1318":"noin 1318","1292":"1292","1322":"1322","1320":"1320","Abt 1320 ":"noin 1320","Abt 1322 Of, Misterton, Leic, England":"noin 1322","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Misterton, Leicestershire, England":"Misterton, Leicestershire, England","Leicestershire England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Misterton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Misterton, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1296  –":"environ 1296–Décédée","1292–1360":"1292–1360","1318–1385":"1318–1385","1320–Male":"1320–Décédé","1322–Male":"1322–Décédé","1328–1371":"1328–1371","1296–Female":"1296–Décédée","1385":"1385","1296":"1296","Abt 1296  ":"environ 1296","1371":"1371","1360":"1360","Abt 1318":"environ 1318","1292":"1292","1322":"1322","1320":"1320","Abt 1320 ":"environ 1320","Abt 1322 Of, Misterton, Leic, England":"environ 1